section.t:
The 8bit MIME transport extension is laid out as follows: the name of the SMTP service extension defined here is 8bit-MIMEtransport;
the EHLO keyword value associated with the extension is 8BITMIME;
no parameter is used with the 8BITMIME EHLO keyword;
one optional parameter using the keyword BODY is added to the MAIL FROM command. The value associated with this parameter is a keyword indicating whether a 7bit message (in strict compliance with ) or a MIME message (in strict compliance with ) with arbitrary octet content is being sent. The syntax of the value is as follows, using the ABNF notation of : body-value ::= "7BIT" / "8BITMIME"
no additional SMTP verbs are defined by this extension; and,
the next section specifies how support for the extension affects the behavior of a server and client SMTP.
